The Rand is influenced by the economic and political stability of South Africa’s trading partners. China is the leading export destination for South African goods. As a result, the political and economic climate in China has a significant impact on the performance and value of the South African Rand. Global market uncertainty
Uncertainty in the global markets can cause currency prices to fluctuate often. Here are a few examples of worldwide events that have had an impact on the Rand in the recent decade. Prices of commodities
South Africa is a large exporter of raw materials. It is the world’s largest platinum exporter. For the year 2019, its GDP is $351.4 billion dollars, with a GDP per capita of $6,001.4. Interest Rates Interest rates are another tool to keep an eye on. If interest rates on bank loans rise, it will hurt the economy, causing it to decline and, as a result, the value of the Rand to fall. Government debt Government debt can affect investor confidence and, as a result, the amount of money flowing into the economy. The Rand exchange rate will rise in favour of the South African Rand if inflows are high. Speculators: The USD/Rand exchange rate is frequently influenced by speculators. They hoard money in the hopes of making a profit, forcing the Rand to fall even further. This article was originally published on Nigeria News The Nigerian naira is overvalued by 11.8 percent, a BusinessDay analysis using a Burger King Whopper Index has shown. In 1986, The Economist magazine famously created its Big Mac Index, a guide to the fair value of a currency based on the principle of Purchasing-Power Parity (PPP), which states that… In "Slider 1" Oil is near $72 a barrel Thursday as the South African rand holds at its best level since 2019 with most Asian stocks climbing and U.S. equity contracts steady, weathering the latest twist in the U.S.-China relationship as well as comments from the Federal Reserve on a potential reduction in… In "Business" ENaira to Dollar Exchange Rate Today 3rd January 2022 eNaira price exchange rate today, since the introduction of the eNaira, the currency has been paired against the Dollar currency to enable the world to understand the value of one against the other. You will recall that the eNaira is a… In "Breaking News" Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!